profile_positions.description:
* A non-profit organization  - I, together with Geraldine Manson, were the co-founders' of the WE CARE Trust, a non-profit organisation which addressed the issue of race relations in South Africa. 
* The main objective of the CARE programme was to break down prejudice and to participate in the reconstruction and development programme of South Africa by empowering participants to develop:
* A critical awareness of self, their community, and the South African environment;
* A greater understanding of that which is common and that which is diverse in society;
* Tolerance of self and others;
* An understanding of the nature of change, and so equip youngsters that they are able to cope with change;
* The ability to take control of their own lives and destinies and in turn act as catalysts for change in their societies/communities.
BREAKING DOWN PREJUDICE: When we learn to face the REAL ISSUES and resolve the REAL STRUGGLES;
Our own internal wars;
* when we look inside and become aware of the division between our FEAR and our FAITH, our HEAD and our HEART, our EGO and our SOUL, only then will we be able to
EMBRACE OUR DIFFERENCES AND HONOUR OUR SIMILARITIES.
* The WE CARE Trust was awarded the 1997 French Republic Award for Human Rights.
* It was one of 12 South African and 73 international applicants who applied for the 1997 French Republic Award for Human Rights. 
* The prize was awarded for its "anti-racist education" programme directed at children aged between 10 and 12, along with four other organisations respectively from Columbia, Switzerland, Togo, and Ukraine.
